Implements [[s-5crl]]

When sandbox is enabled with `autoAllowBashIfSandboxed: true`, automatically allow Bash tool calls without permission prompts.

## Changes to `src/settings.ts`

Add helper function:
```typescript
export function shouldAutoAllowWhenSandboxed(
  toolName: string,
  sandboxConfig?: SandboxConfig
): boolean {
  if (!sandboxConfig?.enabled) return false;
  if (!sandboxConfig?.autoAllowBashIfSandboxed) return false;

  const bashTools = ['Bash', 'acp__Bash'];
  return bashTools.includes(toolName);
}
```

## Changes to `src/acp-agent.ts`

Modify `canUseTool()` callback:
```typescript
canUseTool(sessionId: string): CanUseTool {
  return async (toolName, input) => {
    // Auto-allow sandboxed bash
    if (shouldAutoAllowWhenSandboxed(toolName, this.sandboxConfig)) {
      return true;
    }

    // ... existing permission logic
  };
}
```

## Rationale
When sandboxed, bash commands are already restricted by the OS-level sandbox. The permission prompt becomes redundant since the sandbox prevents dangerous operations anyway. This matches Claude Code's behavior.

